recT5Pc6wmONxUJIp","label":"mentions"}],"verses":[{"id":"rec80EjBpcYgZkXJ8","ref":"Luke.1.1","text":"Forasmuch as many have taken in hand to set forth in order a declaration of those things which are most surely believed among us,","year":-5},{"id":"rectxvOjOe0QaHzkP","ref":"Luke.1.2","text":"Even as they delivered them unto us, which from the beginning were eyewitnesses, and ministers of the word;","year":-5},{"id":"recr18xT3s9RAE0gD","ref":"Luke.1.3","text":"It seemed good to me also, having had perfect understanding of all things from the very first, to write unto thee in order, most excellent Theophilus,","year":-5},{"id":"recRbpZ7i1SPd1304","ref":"Luke.1.4","text":"That thou mightest know the certainty of those things, wherein thou hast been instructed.","year":-5},{"id":"rect4RMLvqaXhSBv9","ref":"Luke.1.5","text":"There was in the days of Herod, the king of Judaea, a certain priest named Zacharias, of the course of Abia: and his wife was of the daughters of Aaron, and her name was Elisabeth.","year":-5},{"id":"recxXf8HrOSkPflkd","ref":"Luke.1.6","text":"And they were both righteous before God, walking in all the commandments and ordinances of the Lord blameless.","year":-5}]}
